1. The route assertion incorrectly treats `approved` as an unfiltered request, aborting the mocked response and allowing a real unauthenticated backend call.
2. The malformed-response step re-selects an already-selected status, so React emits no change and no malformed request.
3. The second assertion is only a cascade from the first route-handler failure rather than a production transport defect.

I’ll record the repair plan, then inspect the spec and use this one-test loop to falsify these in order.
